person doing the worship, he should&#39;ve given the benefit of dou=\r\nbt and assumed it was a sincere devotee, rather than assuming it was a fool=\r\n.\n\nSee, when Ramakrishna went there and saw Trilinga Swami, he immediately =\r\nknew the stature and remarked that this is Viswanatha himself. However, oth=\r\ners may not be so fortunate. You only saw a body with some body parts and s=\r\nome clothes and nothing beyond it. If so, give the benefit of doubt and tre=\r\nat kindly and respectfully. Just because of external parameters, do not jud=\r\nge a person and act harsh.\n\nHitting a person who still has a limited self-i=\r\ndentification is one thing and hitting a person who has no limited self-ide=\r\nntification and identifies with the entire universe or with a deity is diff=\r\nerent.\n\n* * *\n\nIn any case, do not worry about that priest that much. For a=\r\nll you know, he may be an associate of Shiva who came along with Trilinga S=\r\nwami to enact a story and teach a moral and he may have gone back to Shiva.=\r\n Even if not, he was lucky to enact an important role in an interesting div=\r\nine drama.\n\n* * *\n\nJeevanmuktas may engage in actions that are difficult to=\r\n comprehend. They have no personal ego, will and agenda. They become instru=\r\nments for Nature to fulfil the Natural order. The action of Trilinga Swami =\r\nmay help several people question, challenge and overcome their biases and l=\r\nearn some important lessons, centuries after he left earth.\n\n* * *\n\nRegardi=\r\nng many gods: As I keep emphasizing, yogis and saints sometimes give advice=\r\ns based on desa-kaala-paatra or advices geared at a specific set of people.=\r\n\n\nThere is nothing wrong in having many deities in pooja room and worshippi=\r\nng all. Such people may lead fruitful dharmik lives. However, Vimalananda m=\r\nay not be concerned about such people. His teachings may be addressed at so=\r\nme other people to come in the coming years who he has rina with and who ar=\r\ne meant to achieve saayujya of some deities and do some work. There is an i=\r\nntended audience for every work and no work can be perfect for all audience=\r\n.\n\nIf the goal is either liberation or a deity&#39;s darshan (vision) or saayuj=\r\nya (company), one has to agree that focusing on one deity is the best thing=\r\n to do, rather than trying to focus mind on ten deities and keep switching.=\r\n A deity comes when mind and its thoughts are filled with that deity&#39;s name=\r\n and mantra and other thoughts are driven away from the mind. Vimalananda p=\r\nerhaps wanted to motivate several people to strive for vision/company of de=\r\nities. He probably thought some people he has a rina with would come to ear=\r\nth with such a potential.\n\n* * *\n\nThyagaraja did compose songs on many deit=\r\nies. But, he first had a darshan of Rama. He spent several years chanting R=\r\nama&#39;s name and had a darshan. Then he composed songs on many deities. Howev=\r\ner, he saw all of them as different emanations from Rama. He saw Rama in al=\r\nl.\n\nSame with Aadi Shankara, Muththuswamy Deekshitar, Bammera Pothana and o=\r\nthers.\n\nWhen one achieves perfection in surrender to one deity, one&#39;s life =\r\nis made. After that, one will see the same deity in all deities even if he =\r\nworships 100 deities. If one is switching between ten deities before that, =\r\nit may not be helpful in filling the mind with thoughts of any of those dei=\r\nties. Mind sees those deities as different objects and may not fully surren=\r\nder to any of them. Still, as I said, one may lead a fruitful dhaarmik life=\r\n. That&#39;s fine.\n\nBut, if you really want to taste the nectar of complete sur=\r\nrender, it is better to pick one deity and fill the mind with his/her thoug=\r\nhts.\n\n* * *\n\n&gt; Excellent answers on each thread and mother showed her divin=\r\ne\n&gt; grace through you that I am able to find answers to many\n&gt; questions th=\r\nat my immature mind kee