taker, just as a servant may be living in a rich person&#39;s ho=\r\nuse as the caretaker as that person stays away. Think of all that is in you=\r\nr hands as the sacred property of your master and take care like a committe=\r\nd servant. A servant takes the best care of his master&#39;s property, but does=\r\n not get attached. Do not be attached anything and yet take the best possib=\r\nle care. If something goes wrong, do not worry too much and tell yourself t=\r\nhat the master will take care of it when he gets a chance to look at it. Th=\r\nink for a moment how a servant taking care of the properties of a master li=\r\nving away thinks and behaves.\n&gt; \n&gt; If one can attain the spirit and mental =\r\nstate of the servant in this analogy, one&#39;s life will be made.\n&gt; \n&gt; * * *\n&gt;=\r\n \n&gt; Read what Manish wrote below:\n&gt; \n&gt; &lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;Once you take Time out of the eq=\r\nuation (because a deity has a different time space frame which runs in thou=\r\nsands of years which pass by in a blink of an eye) by waiting with patience=\r\n, then where will God go? God has to come, He can&#39;t escape.&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt; \n&gt; Take t=\r\nime out of the equation, i.e. do not put a time limit or say &quot;I have done t=\r\nhis sadhana for XYZ years. Why is God not coming?&quot; Wait patiently. After al=\r\nl, if you have truly surrendered, why is it a problem then to wait, let us =\r\nsay, 1000 years for Her grace? If you say &quot;I want Her to come in 1 year or =\r\n10 years and not 1000 years&quot;, that means you have not fully surrendered.\n&gt; =\r\n\n&gt; * * *\n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; How to measure it?\n&gt; \n&gt; One can measure it by seeing how on=\r\ne is internally reacting to challenging circumstances that would earlier pr=\r\novoke lust, anger, greed, jealosy etc inside one.\n&gt; \n&gt; However, what will o=\r\nne do by measuring? It is not like one can turn a knob based on the measure=\r\nment to correct it.\n&gt; \n&gt; In fact